class Workflow(*args, **kwargs)[source]¶

Bases: leukapp.apps.core.models.LeukappModel

Extraction's sequence workflow.

Each Workflow can be linked to multiple Projects using the projects ManyToMany field. Additionally, the attribute projects_string can also be used with _get_projects_from_string() to link projects and workflows:

# This will add projects 101 and 102 to Workflow when saving
projects_string = '101-102-103'
APP_NAME = 'workflows'¶

Name of the application where Workflow is contained.

extraction¶

ForeignKey to the Extraction model.

ext_id = None¶

ID used by the sequencing CENTER to identify the Workflow.

The default value is UNKNOWN because most likely, scientist don’t know this ID when they are submitting Workflows to leukgen.

int_id = None¶

Internal ID used to describe the Workflow object.

This value is generated by _get_int_id() and it includes crucial information separated by a - character. For example, the internal code 1-1A-S100-x10-CMO will refer to:

  • 1: count of Workflows per Extraction, see: workflows_count.
  • 1A: technology/technology_type internal code based on the custom dictionary INT_ID_TECHNOLOGY.
  • S100: Internal code for the read_length/read_type combination. see INT_ID_READ_LENGTH and INT_ID_READ_TYPE.
  • X10: sequencing_platform internal code. See: INT_ID_PLATFORM.
  • CMO: sequencing_center internal code. See: INT_ID_CENTER.
